---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Random Number Generator" url="https://www.desktools.tk/random-number-generator/"
    description="Generate random numbers quickly and easily with our online random number generator. Choose the number of random numbers you want, the range of numbers, and whether you want the numbers to be unique or repeating.">
    <main>
        <div class="col-md-8 mb-4">
            <h2 id="intro-heading">Create Passphrases with this Online Generator</h2>
            <p>Create passphrases that can be used as online passwords on any sites.</p>
            <p>Click the generate button to create a new password. You can also edit it to your liking.</p>
        </div>


        <div class="card mb-5">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h1 class="card-title">Password Generator From Words</h1>
                <div class="row mb-4">
                    <div class="col md-12 position-relative">
                        <textarea type="text" id="number" class="form-control"></textarea>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mb-4">
                    <div class="col md-4">
                        <label for="range" class="form-label">Number of Words</label>
                        <br>
                        <input type="number" name="" id="amount" value="1" min="1" max="1000" class="form-control">
                    </div>
                    <div class="col md-4">
                        <label for="range" class="form-label">Minimum</label>
                        <br>
                        <input type="number" name="" id="min" value="1" min="1" max="10000" class="form-control">
                    </div>
                    <div class="col md-4">
                        <label for="range" class="form-label">Maximum</label>
                        <br>
                        <input type="number" name="" id="max" value="100" min="1" max="10000" class="form-control">
                    </div>
                </div>
                <button id="btn" class="btn btn-primary">Generate</button>
            </div>
        </div>

        <article class="card p-4">
            <div class="col-md-8">
                <h2>What is a random number generator?</h2>
                <p>A random number generator is a mathematical tool or algorithm used to generate a sequence of random
                    numbers. These numbers are usually generated using a computer program.</p>
                <p>Use the numbers: You can use the generated numbers for whatever purpose you desire. This
                    might involve analyzing the numbers for statistical purposes, using the numbers in a
                    computer simulation, or incorporating the numbers into a game or other application.</p>
                <p>Random number generators can be used to generate numbers with a variety of different properties, such
                    as numbers that are uniformly distributed over a given range, numbers that follow a certain
                    probability distribution, or numbers that are independently and identically distributed (i.i.d).</p>
                <h2>How are the numbers generated?</h2>
                <p>There are many different algorithms and techniques that can be used to generate random numbers, and
                    the choice of algorithm will depend on the specific requirements of the application. Some common
                    methods for generating random numbers include the use of hardware random number generators,
                    pseudo-random number generators, and true random number generators.</p>
                <p>Numbers generated on this site are generated in JavaScript by using the Math.random() method.</p>
                <h2>How do I use it?</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p><strong>Specify the parameters:</strong> Choose the number of random numbers you want to generate, the range
                            of numbers by selecting a minimum and maximum value.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p><strong>Generate the numbers:</strong> Click the generate button the random number(s). The
                            numbers will be displayed in a list or other the textfield.</p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </article>
    </main>
</Layout>

<script is:inline>
    document.querySelector('#btn').addEventListener('click', generateNumber)

    function generateNumber() {

        const amount = document.querySelector('#amount').value

        const arr = []
        for (let i = 0; i < amount; i++) {
            const n = randomNumber(document.querySelector('#min').value, document.querySelector('#max').value)
            arr.push(n)
        }

        document.querySelector('#number').value = arr.join(' ')
    }

    function randomNumber(min, max) {
        const minimum = Math.ceil(min)
        const maximum = Math.floor(max)
        return Math.floor(Math.random() * (maximum + 1 - minimum) + minimum)
    }

    document.querySelector('#min').addEventListener('change', (e)=>{
        const value = parseInt(e.target.value)
        const max = parseInt(document.querySelector('#max').value)
        if(value >= max){
            e.target.value = max - 1
        }
    })

</script>